		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=69092"><span class="Sage">Kakar the Vile</span></a><b><span class="Sage"><br/>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="112" width="108" src="http://allakhazam.com/uf/Kakar/Hunter.jpg" /><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />4062 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=6;mid=1135141297565815;page=1;howmany=50#1135141297565815"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><a href="HTTP://www.redmaces.org/paladin/index.htm" title="HTTP://www.redmaces.org/paladin/index.htm" target="akztarg">Here's</a> a very useful link.  It's the Paladin Pamphlet, and has a lot of general knowledge stuff.  Another <a href="HTTP://www.pon.myfreebb.com/index.php" title="HTTP://www.pon.myfreebb.com/index.php" target="akztarg">link</a> is to the Paladins of Norrath site. <br /> <br />Some general stuff.  Usually as a paladin you are going to be the main tank in experience groups.  Establishing aggro is the key, and our ability to get aggro quickly and keep it is one of the most key traits of our class.  Use your stuns, a lot.  They piss the mobs off and keep them hitting you in stead of someone else.  Yes, taunt helps.  Rooting a mob and staying close to it helps.  There are other tricks that arguably help such as using flash of light, beg, disarm, etc.  But in all honesty if you are using your stuns correctly and the occasional taunt and root that's all you really need. <br /> <br />Positioning is also handy.  You'll often hear players complaining about getting a mob off the wall (rangers).  One of the handy tools in our stuns is the push in some of them.  Particularly the ones that do damage.  Those typically have a push effect, which you can direct.  The push will be whatever way you are facing, so if you got a mob in a wall, you can cast one of these push stuns and turn in the direction away from the wall which will move the mob in that direction. <br /> <br />Another role we fill effectively is crowd control.  Root parking, off tanking, and helping other CC folks is an important task.  Enchanters and shaman, and bards as well, can draw a lot of aggro debuffing and mezzing mobs.  If you are in a group or raid and a chanter or bard has a mob mezzed, it's always good to root them and throw a couple NON-DAMAGING stuns on.  This will draw aggro off the mezzer and have them head for you if the mezz breaks early.  After all, we can take a heck of a lot more of a beating than an enchanter.  Also, shaman slowing and debuffing mobs also appreciate this tactic.  It's good to keep an eye on these folks health as well, throwing a quick heal on them now and then can make the difference between a happy chanter/shammy and one that had to suffer through multiple rezzes during a raid or exp group. <br /> <br />Off tanking is often an important role as well.  Some mobs can't be mezzed, so if you're on a raid or group with those types of mobs, and you have a warrior or another tank filling the MT role, you'll have to be aware of mobs that need to be kept busy while the rest of the group/raid concentrates on assisting the main tank.  Paladins fill this role well due to our ability to heal ourselves and quick aggro. <br /> <br />Rampage tanking is also another task we're usually taking care of.  If a mob rampages and starts doing damage to those on the top of the aggro list, it's generally better to have a paladin taking those hits than a cleric.  This can be tricky, often being one of the first to do damage will help you be on the rampage list.  So throwing a quick damaging stun as the mob is incoming, or shooting a bow at it (often less effective as we miss a lot) or even pulling the mob if at all possible and letting the tank take aggro are all tricks to getting on the rampage list. <br /> <br />Finally, knowing the abilities of other classes is handy.  For instance, nothing irritates a rogue more than a tank that moves around a lot.  They need to be behind the mob to do the most damage, so getting into a routine when bringing in a mob helps a lot.  Like if you are fighting in the same spot for a while, engaging in the same location and turning the same way every time lets people know what to expect and get into a rhythm.  <br /> <br />Just a few things off the top of my head.  The PoN site is an excellent source of information for many tips.  It's not nearly as active as it once was, but there are still a lot of good posts there, and people who know what you're talking about if you ask a good question.</p>
